You're right that the problem was not particularly an XML error but lay within the rather arcane Perl script 
that helps parse the XML (carter.pl).  Near the end of that file, you'll see a "cross references" section that matches 
up various "xref to" statements with their HTML links.  I've added a new one, named "Ext3" to the list.  Each new 
link will require a similar statement in the carter.pl file with the same format (including the ugly \/ notation for 
any forward slashes in the URL or HTML tags).


There was not a similar process for images, so I've added one directly after the cross references section.  It matches 
up (actually replaces) any use of in the XML file with the appropriate image file. 



